    "custom_heritage_homepage": {
      "type": "custom-heritage",
      "settings": {
        "image_aspect_ratio": "1 \/ 1",
        "layout": "image_left",
        "subtitle": "THE ART OF DEG & BHAPKA",
        "title": "Distilled In Kannauj, Perfume Capital of India",
        "heading_size": "h1",
        "text": "<p>Since ancient times, Kannauj has kept the heritage of perfume distillation alive. Using the traditional Deg-Bhapka process, flowers and natural raw materials are distilled in copper pots over wood fires, sending fragrant steam to rest in cold clay containers base-filled with sandalwood oil.<\/p><p>Mahekh preserves this pure artisan process, providing long-lasting attars free from chemicals and alcohol.<\/p>",
        "button_label": "Explore Our Process",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-2",
        "padding_top": 44,
        "padding_bottom": 44
      }
    },
